---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "22 June 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Dennis Özmen"
  description="How personal data is collected and processed on dennisozmen.com."
>
  <article
    class="relative z-20 w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-16 sm:mt-24 mb-16 px-4 sm:px-7 lg:px-0"
  >
    <header>
      <h1
        class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl"
      >
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-500">
        Last updated: {lastUpdated}
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert max-w-none mt-8">
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains what personal data is collected when you
        visit <strong>dennisozmen.com</strong> ("this website"), how it is used,
        and what rights you have. Processing is carried out in accordance with the
        EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and applicable German law.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Controller</h2>
      <p>
        The party responsible for data processing on this website is:
      </p>
      <p>
        Dennis Özmen<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@dennisozmen.com">privacy@dennisozmen.com</a>
      </p>

      <h2>2. Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        This website is hosted by Vercel Inc., 340 S Lemon Ave #4133, Walnut, CA
        91789, USA. When you access the site, the hosting provider automatically
        collects and stores server log data that your browser transmits — in
        particular your IP address, browser type and version, operating system,
        the referring URL, and the date and time of access. This data is processed
        to ensure a secure, stable, and reliable service.
      </p>
      <p>
        Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in the secure
        operation of the website). Processing may involve a transfer of data to
        the USA, safeguarded by appropriate measures such as Standard Contractual
        Clauses and the EU–US Data Privacy Framework. See Vercel's privacy policy:
        <a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
          >vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy</a
        >.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Cookies and consent</h2>
      <p>
        On your first visit, a consent banner is shown. The site distinguishes two
        categories:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Necessary</strong> — required for the site to function, e.g. a
          cookie storing your consent choice (<code>cc_cookie</code>) and your
          theme preference (stored in your browser's local storage). These are set
          on the basis of Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics</strong> — only set <em>after</em> you opt in (see
          section 4), on the basis of Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (consent).
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You can change or withdraw your consent at any time via the
        <strong>"Cookie settings"</strong> link in the footer. Withdrawal does not
        affect the lawfulness of processing carried out before withdrawal.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Google Analytics 4 (via Google Tag Manager)</h2>
      <p>
        This website uses Google Analytics 4, a web analytics service, loaded
        through Google Tag Manager. The provider is Google Ireland Limited, Gordon
        House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland ("Google"). Google Analytics uses
        cookies (e.g. <code>_ga</code>) and processes usage data such as the pages
        you visit, approximate location derived from your IP address, and device
        and browser information, in order to analyse how the website is used.
      </p>
      <p>
        Analytics are only activated <strong>after you give consent</strong>.
        Google Consent Mode v2 is implemented so that no analytics cookies are set
        and no analytics data is collected before consent. Data may be transferred
        to Google LLC in the USA, safeguarded by Standard Contractual Clauses and
        the EU–US Data Privacy Framework.
      </p>
      <p>
        Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (consent). You can withdraw your consent at
        any time via "Cookie settings" in the footer. More information:
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
          >policies.google.com/privacy</a
        >.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Contact form</h2>
      <p>
        If you use the contact form, the data you enter — your name, email address,
        and message — is transmitted via Web3Forms (10Web FZ-LLC), a service that forwards form submissions by email. 
        This data is used solely to process and respond to your enquiry. A honeypot field is used for spam protection. This
        data is used solely to process and respond to your enquiry. A honeypot field
        is used for spam protection.
      </p>
      <p>
        Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR where your enquiry relates to a contract or
        pre-contractual measures, and otherwise Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate
        interest in responding to enquiries). Your data is deleted once your enquiry
        has been dealt with and no statutory retention obligations apply. See
        Web3Forms' privacy policy:
        <a href="https://web3forms.com/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
          >web3forms.com/privacy-policy</a
        >.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Contact by email</h2>
      <p>
        If you contact me directly by email, the information you provide and your
        message are stored in order to handle your request. Legal basis:
        Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR, or Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR where your request relates to a
        contract.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under the GDPR you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>access your personal data (Art. 15);</li>
        <li>rectification of inaccurate data (Art. 16);</li>
        <li>erasure (Art. 17);</li>
        <li>restriction of processing (Art. 18);</li>
        <li>data portability (Art. 20);</li>
        <li>object to processing (Art. 21);</li>
        <li>withdraw consent at any time (Art. 7(3)).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection
        supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR) — in Germany, the authority of your
        federal state. To exercise your rights, contact
        <a href="mailto:privacy@dennisozmen.com">privacy@dennisozmen.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        Personal data is retained only for as long as necessary for the purposes
        described above or as required by applicable statutory retention periods,
        after which it is deleted.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy may be updated to reflect changes to the website or to
        legal requirements. The current version is always available on this page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
